# Prevent text-based three-way merge of sync files.
# These files are auto-exported JSONL data (one JSON object per line).
# Git's line-by-line merge of independently-exported JSONL can produce
# empty or corrupted results. Marking as binary forces a hard conflict
# rather than silent data loss when both sides modify sync files.
# The mergeBranch() function handles this by always preserving the
# target branch version of sync files.
.stoneforge/sync/*.jsonl binary
